            <h2>Buuz</h2>
            <p>
            <p>In Mongolia, "Buuz" is more than just a steamed dumpling; it’s a cherished culinary tradition enjoyed
                during special occasions like Lunar New Year. Made from a soft dough filled with seasoned meat,
                typically mutton or beef, Buuz are shaped into small parcels and steamed to perfection. Affordable and
                hearty, they reflect Mongolia's nomadic roots and reliance on simple, nourishing ingredients. The name
                “Buuz” embodies their essence, meaning “dumpling” in Mongolian. Today, they are a symbol of warmth and
                hospitality, making them a must-try for anyone exploring Mongolian cuisine.</p>
            </p>
