            <h2>Tsuivan</h2>
            <p>Tsuivan, a popular Mongolian stir-fried noodle dish, traces its origins to China and other Asian cuisines
                but has developed its own unique character over time. Known for its simplicity and natural taste,
                Tsuivan is made with handmade noodles, meat (usually mutton or beef), and vegetables like carrots and
                potatoes. Its straightforward preparation and hearty flavors make it a favorite daily meal in most
                Mongolian households. One of its unique traditions is enjoying the leftovers with warm milk tea poured
                over them, creating a comforting and delicious combination. Tsuivan’s wholesome taste and cultural
                significance make it a cherished staple of Mongolian cuisine.</p>
            <img src="/images/mongolia/noodles.jpg" alt="Tsuivan"
