            <h2>Currency</h2>
            <p>
                The Mongolian currency is the **Tögrög (MNT)**, introduced in 1925 as the country’s official currency,
                replacing the use of foreign currencies like the Russian ruble and Chinese yuan. Its name, meaning
                "circle" in Mongolian, reflects the shape of the original coins. Issued by the Bank of Mongolia, the
                Tögrög comes in both coins and vibrant banknotes featuring national heroes like Chinggis Khaan and
                cultural symbols. Its introduction marked a significant step in establishing Mongolia's economic
                independence during the early 20th century. </p>
